The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Pact on infotech centre

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, Sept. 14: Infotech company Rolta will invest Rs 250 crore in setting up an IT development centre in the city over the next five years. 

 The company, a global name in engineering design services and software development, signed a memorandum of understanding with the government today. Its centre will cover five acres at Nonadanga, on the eastern fringes of the city. 

 This is a breakthrough Such companies operate from Hyderabad or Bangalore. This is the first time such a company has come to Calcutta, chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee said. 

 Rolta, which has operations in 35 countries, has bought the land at Rs 1.2 crore an acre. 

 Its chairman and managing director Kamal K. Singh said 4,000 to 5,000 people will be recruited in four to five years. This is just the beginning.




